article.headline: Campbell 69, Lipscomb 68
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Junard Hartley's 3-pointer as time expired gave Campbell a 69-68 victory over Lipscomb on Thursday night. Campbell (6-8, 3-2 Atlantic Sun) pulled even at 66-66 with 45 seconds left on a Matt Gwynne jump shot, marking the first time Lipscomb (6-8, 2-3) didn't have the lead since a tie at 51 with 10:20 to play. From that point, the Bisons scored eight straight points, capped by a tip-in from Brandon Brown with 8:29 to go for a 59-51 advantage. The Camels, who led by 12 points with 1:04 left in the first half, took a 40-33 lead into halftime. With Campbell leading 45-37 with 18:39 left, Lipscomb went on a 12-3 run to lead 49-48 on an Adam Hodzic layup with 12:11 to play. Chris Reynolds scored 12 points for the Camels and Gwynne added 11 and six rebounds. Lipscomb was paced by Hodzic with 14 points and Josh Slater with 13.
